      <div class="msgContentFrame">What Fynlar states is true. <br /> <br />After getting around this crap in the manner I stated above, I have details. <br /> <br />1. You have to find a Martello that hasn't been upgraded. I ran out from the main camp and kept to the left to find Martello 02 which only had 990 energy instead of 2k+. <br /> <br />2. Un-upgraded Martellos do not seem to regenerate at any apparent rate, so it <i>may</i> be possible to do solo. <br /> <br />2. You need <i>four</i> people with MP to be restored to use the Martello to reduce it by 3% each, putting it at 88% so you can recharge it. <br /> <br />It may follow that an upgraded Martello may be depleted to 90% by just seven or eight people, but be wary of the damned thing regenerating a tick and screwing you.<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Solrain wrote:</div><div class="orig">ITT: Hello, my name is Square-Enix. You zerged my Absolute Virtue. Prepare to die.</div></div></div></div>
